WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.659 --> 00:00:03.393
A Veteran's spouse, widow or widower,

2
00:00:03.393 --> 00:00:06.112
minor children and under certain conditions,

3
00:00:06.112 --> 00:00:09.161
unmarried adult children with disabilities

4
00:00:09.161 --> 00:00:11.756
may also be eligible for burial.

5
00:00:11.756 --> 00:00:13.639
Eligible spouses and children may be buried

6
00:00:13.639 --> 00:00:16.384
even if they predecease the Veteran.

7
00:00:16.384 --> 00:00:20.026
VA operates 135 national cemeteries,

8
00:00:20.026 --> 00:00:23.247
and 33 soldiers lots and monument sites in 40 states

9
00:00:23.247 --> 00:00:25.240
and Puerto Rico.

10
00:00:25.240 --> 00:00:28.055
More than four million Americans, including Veterans

11
00:00:28.055 --> 00:00:30.963
of every war and conflict, are buried in VA's

12
00:00:30.963 --> 00:00:32.759
national cemeteries.

13
00:00:32.759 --> 00:00:36.018
VA also provides funding to establish, expand,

14
00:00:36.018 --> 00:00:39.621
improve and maintain 105 Veterans cemeteries

15
00:00:39.621 --> 00:00:41.935
in 47 states and territories,

16
00:00:41.935 --> 00:00:45.036
including tribal trust lands, Guam and Saipan.

